There is something remarkable about our connection to nature that allows us to be uniquely refreshed and recalibrated. Have you ever had an unusually challenging day, only to go outside amongst the trees and grass, with the birds chirping and it all just melts away. How does that feel? 🙏🏼 Just 10 minutes spent outside realigns your circadian clock and is a great cure for jet lag, and you sleep better. Humans are not designed, nor are they created, to be alone and away from nature. We inherently crave connection to those around us, and to the earth. People who have healthy relationships with family and a close circle of friends live longer, and live better. Connect with nature and each other, it's simple and effective. .

Repost from @fortheloveoflyme 😜✨ Embrace your weirdness ✨😜 What makes you weird or different?? Whatever that is, I think it's freakin awesome and I love you weirdos! Weirdness is like a pop of color on a blank canvas. It gives you intrigue, depth, and that unique sparkle that only YOU have. Honestly, weirdness to me is quite endearing so let it shine y'all and stop trying to deny it! Here's some kinda weird things about me : I prefer cold fruit over room temp fruit whether it be bananas, melon, papaya, etc... I need to put 1 or both of my arms under my body to fall asleep and I need to be laying on my stomach. I like the crunching sound peoples feet make when they're hiking in the woods, clipping my nails makes me feel like I have hard boogies, I'm double jointed in my thumbs, and I like wearing clothes that don't match (clearly). 👽 Theres def other weird things about me but that was what first came to mind. So lovely peeps, I wanna know a little more about what makes you "weird" and uniquely special! What I love about sharing our what makes us feel weird or different, is that we no longer feel separate or like we need to keep these parts of us a secret. We can share them and still find love. Sharing our uniqueness actually connects us on a deeper level and a lot of times we find that were actually not all that alone in our weirdness ✨So Feel free to put your weirdness out there and leave it in the comments. I promise I'll only love you more for it. 💞💜💖💚😘😘😘😘😜😜😜
